#include "UserController.h"
#include "AuthService.h"
#include "UserModel.h"
#include "Response.h"

using namespace std;   // â† ØªÙ…Øª Ø§Ù„Ø¥Ø¶Ø§ÙØ© Ù‡Ù†Ø§

crow::response UserController::index(const crow::request& req) {
    string token = req.get_header_value("Authorization");
    User user = AuthService::authenticate(token);
    if (!user.isValid()) return Response::unauthorized();
    if (!AuthService::isAdmin(user)) return Response::forbidden("Only admins can view all users");

    UserModel model;
    auto users = model.all();

    crow::json::wvalue::list userList;
    for (auto& u : users) {
        crow::json::wvalue item;
        item["id"] = u.id;
        item["name"] = u.name;
        item["email"] = u.email;
        item["role"] = u.role;
        userList.push_back(std::move(item));
    }

    crow::json::wvalue data;
    data = std::move(userList);

    return Response::success("Users retrieved", data);
}

crow::response UserController::updateRole(const crow::request& req, int id) {
    string token = req.get_header_value("Authorization");
    User user = AuthService::authenticate(token);
    if (!user.isValid()) return Response::unauthorized();
    if (!AuthService::isAdmin(user)) return Response::forbidden("Only admins can update user roles");

    auto body = crow::json::load(req.body);
    if (!body) return Response::error("Invalid JSON", 400);

    string newRole = body["role"].s();
    if (newRole != "admin" && newRole != "librarian" && newRole != "user")
        return Response::error("Invalid role", 400);

    UserModel model;
    json updates;
    updates["role"] = newRole;

    if (model.update(id, updates)) {
        return Response::success("User role updated successfully");
    }

    return Response::error("User not found", 404);
}

crow::response UserController::destroy(const crow::request& req, int id) {
    string token = req.get_header_value("Authorization");
    User user = AuthService::authenticate(token);
    if (!user.isValid()) return Response::unauthorized();
    if (!AuthService::isAdmin(user)) return Response::forbidden("Only admins can delete users");

    if (user.id == id) return Response::error("You cannot delete yourself", 400);

    UserModel model;
    if (model.deleteById(id)) {
        return Response::success("User deleted successfully");
    }

    return Response::error("User not found", 404);
}

#include "UserController.h"
#include <nlohmann/json.hpp>   // Ù…Ù‡Ù…
using namespace std;

crow::response UserController::index(const crow::request& req) {

    string token = req.get_header_value("Authorization");
    User user = AuthService::authenticate(token);

    if (!user.isValid()) return Response::unauthorized();
    if (!AuthService::isAdmin(user)) return Response::forbidden("Only admins can view all users");

    UserModel model;
    auto users = model.all();

    crow::json::wvalue::list userList;
    for (auto& u : users) {
        crow::json::wvalue item;
        item["id"] = u.id;
        item["name"] = u.name;
        item["email"] = u.email;
        item["role"] = u.role;
        userList.push_back(std::move(item));
    }

    crow::json::wvalue data;
    data["users"] = std::move(userList);

    return Response::success("Users retrieved", data);
}


crow::response UserController::updateRole(const crow::request& req, int id) {

    string token = req.get_header_value("Authorization");
    User user = AuthService::authenticate(token);

    if (!user.isValid()) return Response::unauthorized();
    if (!AuthService::isAdmin(user)) return Response::forbidden("Only admins can update user roles");

    auto body = crow::json::load(req.body);
    if (!body) return Response::error("Invalid JSON", 400);

    string newRole = body["role"].s();
    if (newRole != "admin" && newRole != "librarian" && newRole != "user")
        return Response::error("Invalid role", 400);

    UserModel model;

    nlohmann::json updates;        // â† ØªØµØ­ÙŠØ­
    updates["role"] = newRole;

    if (model.update(id, updates)) {
        return Response::success("User role updated successfully");
    }

    return Response::error("User not found", 404);
}


crow::response UserController::destroy(const crow::request& req, int id) {

    string token = req.get_header_value("Authorization");
    User user = AuthService::authenticate(token);

    if (!user.isValid()) return Response::unauthorized();
    if (!AuthService::isAdmin(user)) return Response::forbidden("Only admins can delete users");

    if (user.id == id)
        return Response::error("You cannot delete yourself", 400);

    UserModel model;

    if (model.deleteById(id)) {
        return Response::success("User deleted successfully");
    }

    return Response::error("User not found", 404);
}

static User fromJson(const json &j) {
    User u;
    if(j.contains("id")) u.id = j["id"].get<int>();
    if(j.contains("name")) u.name = j["name"].get<string>();
    if(j.contains("email")) u.email = j["email"].get<string>();
    if(j.contains("password")) u.password = j["password"].get<string>();

    if(j.contains("date_of_birth")) u.dateOfBirth = j["date_of_birth"].get<string>();
    return u;
}

vector<User> search(const string &query) {
    vector<User> results;
    string lowerQuery = toLower(query);

    for(auto &item : all()) {
        if(toLower(item.name).find(lowerQuery) != string::npos || 
           toLower(item.email).find(lowerQuery) != string::npos ||
           toLower(item.phoneNumber).find(lowerQuery) != string::npos) {
            
            results.push_back(item);
        }
    }
    return results;
}

cpp
string toLower(string s) {
    transform(s.begin(), s.end(), s.begin(), ::tolower);
    return s;
}

UserController.cpp

cpp
#include "UserController.h"
#include <nlohmann/json.hpp>
using namespace std;

crow::response UserController::index(const crow::request& req) {
    string token = req.get_header_value("Authorization");
    User user = AuthService::authenticate(token);
    if(!user.isValid()) return Response::unauthorized();
    if(!AuthService::isAdmin(user)) return Response::forbidden("Only admins can view all users");

    UserModel model;
    auto users = model.all();

    crow::json::wvalue::list userList;
    for(auto &u : users) {
        crow::json::wvalue item;
        item["id"] = u.id;
        item["name"] = u.name;
        item["email"] = u.email;
        item["role"] = u.role;
        item["phone_number"] = u.phoneNumber;
        item["date_of_birth"] = u.dateOfBirth;
        userList.push_back(std::move(item));
    }

    crow::json::wvalue data;
    data["users"] = std::move(userList);
    return Response::success("Users retrieved", data);
}

crow::response UserController::create(const crow::request& req) {
    string token = req.get_header_value("Authorization");
    User authUser = AuthService::authenticate(token);
    if(!authUser.isValid()) return Response::unauthorized();
    if(!AuthService::isAdmin(authUser)) return Response::forbidden("Only admins can create users");

    auto body = crow::json::load(req.body);
    if(!body) return Response::error("Invalid JSON", 400);

    string name = body["name"].s();
    string email = body["email"].s();
    string password = body["password"].s();
    string role = body["role"].s();
    string phone = body.contains("phone_number") ? body["phone_number"].s() : "";
    string dob = body.contains("date_of_birth") ? body["date_of_birth"].s() : "";

    UserModel model;
    if(model.findByEmail(email).isValid()) return Response::error("Email already exists", 400);

    User newUser;
    newUser.name = name;
    newUser.email = email;
    newUser.password = password; // Ù„Ø§Ø­Ù‚Ø§Ù‹ Ø§Ø³ØªØ®Ø¯Ù… Hash
    newUser.role = role;
    newUser.phoneNumber = phone;
    newUser.dateOfBirth = dob;

    model.create(newUser);

    return Response::success("User created successfully", newUser.toJson());
}

crow::response UserController::updateRole(const crow::request& req, int id) {
    string token = req.get_header_value("Authorization");
    User authUser = AuthService::authenticate(token);
    if(!authUser.isValid()) return Response::unauthorized();
    if(!AuthService::isAdmin(authUser)) return Response::forbidden("Only admins can update user roles");

    auto body = crow::json::load(req.body);
    if(!body) return Response::error("Invalid JSON", 400);

    string newRole = body["role"].s();
    if(newRole != "admin" && newRole != "librarian" && newRole != "user")
        return Response::error("Invalid role", 400);

    UserModel model;
    User u = model.getUserById(id);
    if(!u.isValid()) return Response::error("User not found", 404);

    nlohmann::json updates;
    updates["role"] = newRole;

    if(model.update(id, updates))
        return Response::success("User role updated successfully");
    return Response::error("Failed to update role", 500);
}

crow::response UserController::destroy(const crow::request& req, int id) {
    string token = req.get_header_value("Authorization");
    User authUser = AuthService::authenticate(token);
    if(!authUser.isValid()) return Response::unauthorized();
    if(!AuthService::isAdmin(authUser)) return Response::forbidden("Only admins can delete users");

    if(authUser.id == id) return Response::error("You cannot delete yourself", 400);

    UserModel model;
    if(model.deleteById(id)) return Response::success("User deleted successfully");
    return Response::error("User not found", 404);
}

crow::response UserController::search(const crow::request& req) {
    string token = req.get_header_value("Authorization");
    User authUser = AuthService::authenticate(token);
    if(!authUser.isValid()) return Response::unauthorized();
    if(!AuthService::isAdmin(authUser)) return Response::forbidden("Only admins can search users");

    auto body = crow::json::load(req.body);
    if(!body) return Response::error("Invalid JSON", 400);

    string query = body["query"].s();
    UserModel model;
    auto results = model.search(query);

    crow::json::wvalue::list listResults;
    for(auto &u : results) {
        crow::json::wvalue item;
        item["id"] = u.id;
        item["name"] = u.name;
        item["email"] = u.email;
        item["role"] = u.role;
        item["phone_number"] = u.phoneNumber;
        item["date_of_birth"] = u.dateOfBirth;
        listResults.push_back(std::move(item));
    }

    crow::json::wvalue data;
    data["results"] = std::move(listResults);
    return Response::success("Search completed", data);
}

crow::response UserController::getUser(const crow::request& req, int id) {
    string token = req.get_header_value("Authorization");
    User authUser = AuthService::authenticate(token);
    if(!authUser.isValid()) return Response::unauthorized();

    UserModel model;
    User u = model.getUserById(id);
    if(!u.isValid()) return Response::error("User not found", 404);

    return Response::success("User retrieved", u.toJson());
}

#include "UserController.h"
#include <nlohmann/json.hpp>
using namespace std;

crow::response UserController::index() {
    UserModel model;
    auto users = model.all();

    crow::json::wvalue::list userList;
    for (auto &u : users) {
        crow::json::wvalue item;
        item["id"] = u.id;
        item["name"] = u.name;
        item["email"] = u.email;
        item["role"] = u.role;
        item["phone_number"] = u.phoneNumber;
        item["date_of_birth"] = u.dateOfBirth;
        userList.push_back(std::move(item));
    }

    crow::json::wvalue data;
    data["users"] = std::move(userList);
    return Response::success("Users retrieved", data);
}

crow::response UserController::create(const crow::request& req) {
    auto body = crow::json::load(req.body);
    if (!body) return Response::error("Invalid JSON", 400);

    User newUser;
    newUser.name = body["name"].s();
    newUser.email = body["email"].s();
    newUser.password = body["password"].s();
    newUser.role = body.contains("role") ? body["role"].s() : "user";
    newUser.phoneNumber = body.contains("phone_number") ? body["phone_number"].s() : "";
    newUser.dateOfBirth = body.contains("date_of_birth") ? body["date_of_birth"].s() : "";

    UserModel model;
    model.create(newUser);

    return Response::success("User created successfully", newUser.toJson());
}

crow::response UserController::updateRole(const crow::request& req, int id) {
    auto body = crow::json::load(req.body);
    if (!body) return Response::error("Invalid JSON", 400);

    string newRole = body["role"].s();
    if (newRole != "admin" && newRole != "librarian" && newRole != "user")
        return Response::error("Invalid role", 400);

    UserModel model;
    User u = model.getUserById(id);
    if (!u.isValid()) return Response::error("User not found", 404);

    nlohmann::json updates;
    updates["role"] = newRole;

    if (model.update(id, updates))
        return Response::success("User role updated successfully");

    return Response::error("Failed to update role", 500);
}

crow::response UserController::destroy(int id) {
    UserModel model;
    if (model.deleteById(id))
        return Response::success("User deleted successfully");

    return Response::error("User not found", 404);
}

crow::response UserController::search(const std::string& query) {
    UserModel model;
    auto results = model.search(query);

    crow::json::wvalue::list listResults;
    for (auto &u : results) {
        crow::json::wvalue item;
        item["id"] = u.id;
        item["name"] = u.name;
        item["email"] = u.email;
        item["role"] = u.role;
        item["phone_number"] = u.phoneNumber;
        item["date_of_birth"] = u.dateOfBirth;
        listResults.push_back(std::move(item));
    }

    crow::json::wvalue data;
    data["results"] = std::move(listResults);
    return Response::success("Search completed", data);
}

crow::response UserController::getUser(int id) {
    UserModel model;
    User u = model.getUserById(id);
    if (!u.isValid()) return Response::error("User not found", 404);

UserController userController;

CROW_ROUTE(app, "/users").methods("GET"_method)([&](){ return userController.index(); });
CROW_ROUTE(app, "/users").methods("POST"_method)([&](const crow::request& req){ return userController.create(req); });

    auto body = crow::json::load(req.body);
    string q = body["query"].s();

User struct

cpp
struct User {
    int id;
    string name;
    string email;
    string password;
    string role;          
    string phoneNumber;
    string dateOfBirth;

    User() : id(-1), name(""), email(""), password(""), role("user"), phoneNumber(""), dateOfBirth("") {}

    static User fromJson(const json &j) {
        User u;
        if(j.contains("id")) u.id = j["id"].get<int>();
        if(j.contains("name")) u.name = j["name"].get<string>();
        if(j.contains("email")) u.email = j["email"].get<string>();
        if(j.contains("password")) u.password = j["password"].get<string>();
        if(j.contains("role")) u.role = j["role"].get<string>();
        if(j.contains("phone_number")) u.phoneNumber = j["phone_number"].get<string>();
        if(j.contains("date_of_birth")) u.dateOfBirth = j["date_of_birth"].get<string>();
        return u;
    }

    json toJson() const {
        return {
            {"id", id},
            {"name", name},
            {"email", email},
            {"password", password},
            {"role", role},
            {"phone_number", phoneNumber},
            {"date_of_birth", dateOfBirth}
        };
    }

    bool isValid() const { return id != -1 && !email.empty(); }
};

  • ÙƒÙ„ Ù…Ø³ØªØ®Ø¯Ù… Ù„Ù‡ IDØŒ Ø§Ø³Ù…ØŒ Ø¥ÙŠÙ…ÙŠÙ„ØŒ ÙƒÙ„Ù…Ø© Ù…Ø±ÙˆØ±ØŒ Ø¯ÙˆØ±ØŒ Ø±Ù‚Ù… Ù‡Ø§ØªÙØŒ ÙˆØªØ§Ø±ÙŠØ® Ù…ÙŠÙ„Ø§Ø¯.

UserModel

cpp
class UserModel : public BaseModel<User> {
  public:
    UserModel() : BaseModel("storage/users.json") {}

    void create(User &user) {
        user.id = generateId();
        json data = getAllJson();
        data.push_back(user.toJson());
        saveJson(data);
    }

    vector<User> search(const string &query) {
        vector<User> results;
        string lowerQuery = toLower(query);

        for(auto &item : all()) {
            if(toLower(item.name).find(lowerQuery) != string::npos || 
               toLower(item.email).find(lowerQuery) != string::npos ||
               toLower(item.phoneNumber).find(lowerQuery) != string::npos) {
                results.push_back(item);
            }
        }
        return results;
    }

    User findByEmail(const string& email){
        for (const auto& user : all()){
            if (user.email == email){
                return user;
            }
        }
        return User();
    }

    User getUserById(int id) {
        for(auto &user : all()) {
            if(user.id == id) return user;
        }
        return User();
    }

  private:
    string toLower(string s) {
        transform(s.begin(), s.end(), s.begin(), ::tolower);
        return s;
    }
};

crow::response UserController::index() {
    UserModel model;
    auto users = model.all();
    crow::json::wvalue::list userList;
    for (auto &u : users) {
        crow::json::wvalue item;
        item["id"] = u.id;
        item["name"] = u.name;
        item["email"] = u.email;
        item["role"] = u.role;
        item["phone_number"] = u.phoneNumber;
        item["date_of_birth"] = u.dateOfBirth;
        userList.push_back(std::move(item));
    }
    crow::json::wvalue data;
    data["users"] = std::move(userList);
    return Response::success("Users retrieved", data);
}

#pragma once
#include "../../models/User/User.h"
#include "../../core/Response.hpp"
#include <crow.h>

class UserController {
public:
    // GET /users
    crow::response index();

    // POST /users
    crow::response create(const crow::request& req);

    // PUT /users/<id>/role
    crow::response updateRole(const crow::request& req, int id);

    // DELETE /users/<id>
    crow::response destroy(int id);

    // POST /users/search
    crow::response search(const crow::request& req);

    // GET /users/<id>
    crow::response getUser(int id);
};

âœ… UserController.cpp

cpp
#include "UserController.h"
using namespace std;

crow::response UserController::index() {
    UserModel model;
    auto users = model.all();

    crow::json::wvalue::list userList;
    for (auto& u : users) {
        crow::json::wvalue item;
        item["id"] = u.id;
        item["name"] = u.name;
        item["email"] = u.email;
        item["role"] = u.role;
        item["phone_number"] = u.phoneNumber;
        item["date_of_birth"] = u.dateOfBirth;
        userList.push_back(std::move(item));
    }

    crow::json::wvalue data;
    data["users"] = std::move(userList);

    return Response::success("Users retrieved", data);
}

crow::response UserController::create(const crow::request& req) {
    auto body = crow::json::load(req.body);
    if (!body) return Response::error("Invalid JSON", 400);

    UserModel model;
    
    string email = body["email"].s();
    if (model.findByEmail(email).isValid()) {
        return Response::error("Email already exists", 400);
    }

    User newUser;
    newUser.name = body["name"].s();
    newUser.email = email;
    newUser.password = body["password"].s();
    newUser.role = body.contains("role") ? body["role"].s() : "user";
    newUser.phoneNumber = body.contains("phone_number") ? body["phone_number"].s() : "";
    newUser.dateOfBirth = body.contains("date_of_birth") ? body["date_of_birth"].s() : "";

    model.create(newUser);
    return Response::success("User created successfully", newUser.toJson());
}

crow::response UserController::updateRole(const crow::request& req, int id) {
    auto body = crow::json::load(req.body);
    if (!body) return Response::error("Invalid JSON", 400);

    string newRole = body["role"].s();
    if (newRole != "admin" && newRole != "librarian" && newRole != "user") {
        return Response::error("Invalid role", 400);
    }

    UserModel model;
    User u = model.getUserById(id);
    if (!u.isValid()) return Response::error("User not found", 404);

    nlohmann::json updates;
    updates["role"] = newRole;

    if (model.update(id, updates)) {
        return Response::success("Role updated successfully");
    }

    return Response::error("Failed to update role", 500);
}

crow::response UserController::destroy(int id) {
    UserModel model;

    if (model.deleteById(id))
        return Response::success("User deleted successfully");

    return Response::error("User not found", 404);
}

crow::response UserController::search(const crow::request& req) {
    auto body = crow::json::load(req.body);
    if (!body) return Response::error("Invalid JSON", 400);

    string query = body["query"].s();

    UserModel model;
    auto results = model.search(query);

    crow::json::wvalue::list resultList;
    for (auto &u : results) {
        crow::json::wvalue item;
        item["id"] = u.id;
        item["name"] = u.name;
        item["email"] = u.email;
        item["role"] = u.role;
        item["phone_number"] = u.phoneNumber;
        item["date_of_birth"] = u.dateOfBirth;
        resultList.push_back(std::move(item));
    }

    crow::json::wvalue data;
    data["results"] = std::move(resultList);

    return Response::success("Search completed", data);
}

crow::response UserController::getUser(int id) {
    UserModel model;
    User u = model.getUserById(id);

    if (!u.isValid()) return Response::error("User not found", 404);

    return Response::success("User retrieved", u.toJson());
}

cpp
#pragma once
#include "../../models/User/User.h"
#include "../../core/Response.hpp"
#include <crow.h>

class UserController {
public:
    crow::response index();
    crow::response create(const crow::request& req);
    crow::response updateRole(const crow::request& req, int id);
    crow::response destroy(int id);
    crow::response search(const crow::request& req);
    crow::response getUser(int id);
};

âœ… UserController.cpp (Ø¨Ø¯ÙˆÙ† Comments)

cpp
#include "UserController.h"
using namespace std;

crow::response UserController::index() {
    UserModel model;
    auto users = model.all();

    crow::json::wvalue::list userList;
    for (auto& u : users) {
        crow::json::wvalue item;
        item["id"] = u.id;
        item["name"] = u.name;
        item["email"] = u.email;
        item["role"] = u.role;
        item["phone_number"] = u.phoneNumber;
        item["date_of_birth"] = u.dateOfBirth;
        userList.push_back(std::move(item));
    }

    crow::json::wvalue data;
    data["users"] = std::move(userList);

    return Response::success("Users retrieved", data);
}

crow::response UserController::create(const crow::request& req) {
    auto body = crow::json::load(req.body);
    if (!body) return Response::error("Invalid JSON", 400);

    UserModel model;
    string email = body["email"].s();

    if (model.findByEmail(email).isValid())
        return Response::error("Email already exists", 400);

    User newUser;
    newUser.name = body["name"].s();
    newUser.email = email;
    newUser.password = body["password"].s();
    newUser.role = body.contains("role") ? body["role"].s() : "user";
    newUser.phoneNumber = body.contains("phone_number") ? body["phone_number"].s() : "";
    newUser.dateOfBirth = body.contains("date_of_birth") ? body["date_of_birth"].s() : "";

    model.create(newUser);
    return Response::success("User created successfully", newUser.toJson());
}

crow::response UserController::updateRole(const crow::request& req, int id) {
    auto body = crow::json::load(req.body);
    if (!body) return Response::error("Invalid JSON", 400);

    string newRole = body["role"].s();
    if (newRole != "admin" && newRole != "librarian" && newRole != "user")
        return Response::error("Invalid role", 400);

    UserModel model;
    User u = model.getUserById(id);
    if (!u.isValid()) return Response::error("User not found", 404);

    nlohmann::json updates;
    updates["role"] = newRole;

    if (model.update(id, updates))
        return Response::success("Role updated successfully");

    return Response::error("Failed to update role", 500);
}

crow::response UserController::destroy(int id) {
    UserModel model;

    if (model.deleteById(id))
        return Response::success("User deleted successfully");

    return Response::error("User not found", 404);
}

crow::response UserController::search(const crow::request& req) {
    auto body = crow::json::load(req.body);
    if (!body) return Response::error("Invalid JSON", 400);

    string query = body["query"].s();

    UserModel model;
    auto results = model.search(query);

    crow::json::wvalue::list resultList;
    for (auto &u : results) {
        crow::json::wvalue item;
        item["id"] = u.id;
        item["name"] = u.name;
        item["email"] = u.email;
        item["role"] = u.role;
        item["phone_number"] = u.phoneNumber;
        item["date_of_birth"] = u.dateOfBirth;
        resultList.push_back(std::move(item));
    }

    crow::json::wvalue data;
    data["results"] = std::move(resultList);

    return Response::success("Search completed", data);
}

crow::response UserController::getUser(int id) {
    UserModel model;
    User u = model.getUserById(id);

    if (!u.isValid()) return Response::error("User not found", 404);

    return Response::success("User retrieved", u.toJson());
}

UserController.cpp

cpp
#include <string>
#include <vector>
#include "User.h"
#include "Response.h"
#include "AuthService.h"
#include "crow.h"

using namespace std;

class UserController {
public:
    crow::response index(const crow::request& req) {
        string token = req.get_header_value("Authorization");
        User user = AuthService::authenticate(token);
        if (!user.isValid()) return Response::unauthorized();
        if (!AuthService::isAdmin(user)) return Response::forbidden("Only admins can view all users");

        UserModel model;
        auto users = model.all();

        crow::json::wvalue::list userList;
        for (auto& u : users) {
            crow::json::wvalue item;
            item["id"] = u.id;
            item["name"] = u.name;
            item["email"] = u.email;
            item["role"] = u.role;
            itemList.push_back(std::move(item));
        }

        crow::json::wvalue data;
        data = std::move(userList);

        return Response::success("Users retrieved", data);
    }

    crow::response updateRole(const crow::request& req, int id) {
        string token = req.get_header_value("Authorization");
        User user = AuthService::authenticate(token);
        if (!user.isValid()) return Response::unauthorized();
        if (!AuthService::isAdmin(user)) return Response::forbidden("Only admins can update user roles");

        auto body = crow::json::load(req.body);
        if (!body) return Response::error("Invalid JSON", 400);

        string newRole = body["role"].s();
        if (newRole != "admin" && newRole != "librarian" && newRole != "user")
            return Response::error("Invalid role", 400);

        UserModel model;
        json updates;
        updates["role"] = newRole;

        if (model.update(id, updates)) {
            return Response::success("User role updated successfully");
        }

        return Response::error("User not found", 404);
    }

    crow::response destroy(const crow::request& req, int id) {
        string token = req.get_header_value("Authorization");
        User user = AuthService::authenticate(token);
        if (!user.isValid()) return Response::unauthorized();
        if (!AuthService::isAdmin(user)) return Response::forbidden("Only admins can delete users");

        if (user.id == id) return Response::error("You cannot delete yourself", 400);

        UserModel model;
        if (model.deleteById(id)) {
            return Response::success("User deleted successfully");
        }

        return Response::error("User not found", 404);
    }
};

#include "UserController.h"

crow::response UserController::index(const crow::request& req) {
    string token = req.get_header_value("Authorization");
    User user = AuthService::authenticate(token);
    if (!user.isValid()) return Response::unauthorized();
    if (!AuthService::isAdmin(user)) return Response::forbidden("Only admins can view all users");

    UserModel model;
    auto users = model.all();

    crow::json::wvalue::list userList;
    for (auto& u : users) {
        crow::json::wvalue item;
        item["id"] = u.id;
        item["name"] = u.name;
        item["email"] = u.email;
        item["role"] = u.role;
        userList.push_back(std::move(item));
    }

    crow::json::wvalue data;
    data = std::move(userList);

    return Response::success("Users retrieved", data);
}

crow::response UserController::updateRole(const crow::request& req, int id) {
    string token = req.get_header_value("Authorization");
    User user = AuthService::authenticate(token);
    if (!user.isValid()) return Response::unauthorized();
    if (!AuthService::isAdmin(user)) return Response::forbidden("Only admins can update user roles");

    auto body = crow::json::load(req.body);
    if (!body) return Response::error("Invalid JSON", 400);

    string newRole = body["role"].s();
    if (newRole != "admin" && newRole != "librarian" && newRole != "user")
        return Response::error("Invalid role", 400);

    UserModel model;
    json updates;
    updates["role"] = newRole;

    if (model.update(id, updates)) {
        return Response::success("User role updated successfully");
    }

    return Response::error("User not found", 404);
}

crow::response UserController::destroy(const crow::request& req, int id) {
    string token = req.get_header_value("Authorization");
    User user = AuthService::authenticate(token);
    if (!user.isValid()) return Response::unauthorized();
    if (!AuthService::isAdmin(user)) return Response::forbidden("Only admins can delete users");

    if (user.id == id) return Response::error("You cannot delete yourself", 400);

    UserModel model;
    if (model.deleteById(id)) {
        return Response::success("User deleted successfully");
    }

    return Response::error("User not found", 404);
}
